Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is covered by lakes or ponds that do not intersect the high resolution stream netowork.
Name: openoffnet
Data Source: Fish & Wildlife Service (FWS) Nat ional Wetlands Inventory

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is covered by wetlands, lakes, or ponds that do not intersect the high resolution stream netowork.
Name: alloffnet
Data Source: Fish & Wildlife Service (FWS) Nat ional Wetlands Inventory
Layer Classification:
"WETLAND_TYPE" = 
"Freshwater Emergent Wetland", 
"Freshwater Forested/Shrub Wetland", "Freshwater Pond", 
"Lake", or 
"Other"

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is covered by lakes or ponds that intersect the high resolution stream netowork.
Name: openonnet
Data Source: Fish & Wildlife Service (FWS) Nat ional Wetlands Inventory

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is covered by wetlands, lakes, or ponds that intersect the high resolution stream netowork.
Name: allonnet
Data Source: Fish & Wildlife Service (FWS) Nat ional Wetlands Inventory
Layer Classification:
"WETLAND_TYPE" = 
"Freshwater Emergent Wetland", 
"Freshwater Forested/Shrub Wetland", "Freshwater Pond", 
"Lake", or 
"Other"

Description: The percentage of the catchment areacovered by ponds, lakes, or deep estuary/marine water.
Name: fwsopenwater
Data Source: Fish & Wildlife Service (FWS) Nat ional Wetlands Inventory

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is classified as any type of wetland.
Name: fwswetlands
Data Source: Fish & Wildlife Service (FWS) Nat ional Wetlands Inventory
Layer Classification:
"WETLAND_TYPE" =  
"Estuarine and Marine Wetland", 
"Freshwater Emergent Wetland", or

Description: The contributing drainage area to the downstream point of the catchment.
Name: AreaSqKM
Data Source: High Resolution Delineation

Description: The total wet atmoshpheric deposition of nitrate ion in 2011 spatially averaged over the catchment area.
Name: dep_no3_2011
Data Source: National Atmospheric Deposition Program (NADP)

Description: The total wet atmoshpheric deposition of sulfate ion in 2011 spatially averaged over the catchment area.
Name: dep_so4_2011
Data Source: National Atmospheric Deposition Program (NADP)

Description: The landscape elevation spatially averaged over the catchment area.
Name: elevation
Data Source: National Elevation Dataset (NED) -  processed by UMass

Description: The slope of the landscape spatially averaged over the catchment area.
Name: slope_pcnt
Data Source: National Elevation Dataset (NED) -  processed by UMass

Description: The percentage of the contributing drainage area that is classified as impervious surface.
Name: impervious
Data Source: National Land Cover Database (NLCD) - Impervious

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is covered by agricultural land (e.g. cultivated crops, orchards, and pasture) including fallow land.
Name: agriculture
Data Source: National Land Cover Database (NLCD) - Land Cover
Layer Classification:
"Land_Cover" (Land Cover Class) =  
"Orchards/Vineyards" (61),
"Pasture/Hay" (81),
"Cultivated Crops - row crops" (82),
"Cultivated Crops - small grains" (83), or 
"Fallow" (84)

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is covered by trees taller than 5 meters and dominated by species that lose their foliage in repsonse to season change.
Name: forest_decid
Data Source: National Land Cover Database (NLCD) - Land Cover

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that has been developed by human activity to any extent.
Name: developed
Data Source: National Land Cover Database (NLCD) - Land Cover
Layer Classification:
"Land_Cover" (Land Cover Class) = 
"Developed, Open Space" (21), 
"Developed, Low Intensity" (22), 
"Developed, Medium Intensity" (23), 
"Developed, High Intensity" (24), 
"Unconsolidated Shore/Quarries/Gravel Pits/Strip Mines" (32),  or 
"Urban/Recreational Grasses" (85)

Description: The percentage of the catchment area covered by places where people work or live in high numbers. These areas are typically covered by more than 80% impervious surface.
Name: devel_hi
Data Source: National Land Cover Database (NLCD) - Land Cover

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is covered by areas with a mixture of vegetation and constructed materials, such as single family housing units. These areas are typically covered by 20% - 49% impervious surface.
Name: devel_low
Data Source: National Land Cover Database (NLCD) - Land Cover

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is covered by areas with a mixture of vegetation and constructed materials, such as single family housing units. These areas are typically covered by 50% - 79% impervious surface.
Name: devel_med
Data Source: National Land Cover Database (NLCD) - Land Cover

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is covered by some constructed materials, but mostly lawn grass vegetation such as parks, golf courses, and single family housing units on large lots. These areas are typically covered by less than 20% impervious surface.
Name: devel_opn
Data Source: National Land Cover Database (NLCD) - Land Cover

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is covered by trees taller than 5 meters and dominated by species that maintain foliage year-round.
Name: forest_evgrn
Data Source: National Land Cover Database (NLCD) - Land Cover

Description: The percentage of the catchment area made up of any trees taller than 5 meters.

"Evergreen Forest" (42), 
"Mixed Forest" (43), 
"Woody Wetlands" (90), 
"Palustrine Forested Wetland" (91), or

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is covered by trees taller than 5 meters and not dominated by either evergreen or deciduous.
Name: forest_mixed
Data Source: National Land Cover Database (NLCD) - Land Cover

"Land_Cover" (Land Cover Class) =

"Woody Wetlands" (90),

Description: The percentage of the catchment area covered by open water.
Name: water
Data Source: National Land Cover Database (NLCD) - Land Cover

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is classified as forested land with developed land treated as missing data. This layer serves as an attempt to avoid high correlation between forested and impervious surface in the northeastern U.S.
Name: undev_forest
Data Source: National Land Cover Database (NLCD) - Land Cover
Layer Classification:
"Land_Cover" (Land Cover Class) = 
"Deciduous Forest" (41), 
"Evergreen Forest" (42), 
"Mixed Forest" (43), 
"Woody Wetlands" (90), 
"Palustrine Forested Wetland" (91), 
"Estuarine Forested Wetland" (93)

IN addition, the following get reclassified as NA (-9999):
"Developed, Open Space" (21), 
"Developed, Low Intensity" (22), 
"Developed, Medium Intensity" (23), 
"Developed, High Intensity" (24), 
"Barren Land (Rock/Sand/Clay)" (31), and
"Unconsolidated Shore/Quarries/Gravel Pits/Strip Mines" (32)

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is classified as any type of wetland.
Name: wetland
Data Source: National Land Cover Database (NLCD) - Land Cover

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is covered by a perent soil material with texture described as "sandy".
Name: percent_sandy
Data Source: USDA National Resources Conservation Sciences (NRCS) - Soil Survey Geographic Database (SSURGO)
Layer Classification:
Component Parent Material ("copm") table:
Textural Modifier ("pmmodifier") = 
"Sandy"

Description: The numerical average of the rank of seven drainage class categories over the catchment area. These categories describe the natural drainage conditions of the soil referring to frequency and duration of wet periods. Values range from 1 (Excessively drained) to 7 (Very poorly drained).
Name: drainageclass
Data Source: USDA National Resources Conservation Sciences (NRCS) - Soil Survey Geographic Database (SSURGO)
Layer Classification:
Component ("component") table:
Drainage Class ("drainagecl") column:
"Excessively drained" = 1
"Somewhat excessively drained" = 2
"Well drained" = 3
"Moderately well drained" = 4
"Somewhat poorly drained" = 5
"Poorly drained" = 6
"Very poorly drained" = 7

Description: The percentage of the catchment area with soil classified as hydrologic group A. These soils have a low runoff potential and high infiltration and water transmission rates.
Name: hydrogroup_a
Data Source: USDA National Resources Conservation Sciences (NRCS) - Soil Survey Geographic Database (SSURGO)

Description: The percentage of the catchment area with soil classified as hydrologic groups A or B. These soils have moderate to high infiltration and water transmission rates.
Name: hydrogroup_ab
Data Source: USDA National Resources Conservation Sciences (NRCS) - Soil Survey Geographic Database (SSURGO)

Description: The percentage of the catchment area with soil classified as hydrologic groups C or D. These soils have low to very low infiltration and water transmission rates.
Name: hydrogroup_cd
Data Source: USDA National Resources Conservation Sciences (NRCS) - Soil Survey Geographic Database (SSURGO)

Description: The percentage of the catchment area with soil classified as hydrologic group D, including soils described as group A, B, or C but have a high water table putting them in the D group. These soils have high runoff potential and very low infiltration and water transmission rates.
Name: hydrogroup_d4
Data Source: USDA National Resources Conservation Sciences (NRCS) - Soil Survey Geographic Database (SSURGO)

Description: The percentage of the catchment area with soil classified as hydrologic group D. These soils have high runoff potential and very low infiltration and water transmission rates.
Name: hydrogroup_d1
Data Source: USDA National Resources Conservation Sciences (NRCS) - Soil Survey Geographic Database (SSURGO)

Description: The percentage of the catchment area that is covered by a perent soil material with texture described as "sandy", "gravelly", or a combination of the two.
Name: surfcoarse
Data Source: USDA National Resources Conservation Sciences (NRCS) - Soil Survey Geographic Database (SSURGO)
Layer Classification:
Component Parent Material ("copm") table:
Textural Modifier ("pmmodifier") = 
"Sandy", 
"Sandy and gravelly", or 
"Gravelly"
